data.title: TERITORYO
data.meta_description:
TERITORYO - Free download as Word Doc (.doc), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document provides a brief profile of Pampanga province in the Philippines. Some key details include:
- Pampanga's capital is San Fernando City and it has a population of over 2 million people. 
- The province is known as the Culinary Capital of the Philippines and Kapampangan is the dominant language.
- Major industries include farming, fishing, and handicrafts like parol-making. Rice and fish are major products.
- Pampanga has many heritage churches, historical landmarks, and natural attractions that are popular with tourists.
